# Trailing-slash 301 redirects for SEO canonicalization.
#
# Cloudflare Workers Static Assets emits HTTP 307 for trailing-slash redirects
# (both via html_handling: drop-trailing-slash on prerendered routes and via
# the SSR fall-through on dynamic routes). Search engines treat 307 as
# "temporary, keep checking the original URL" and repeatedly probe the
# slashed variant, surfacing it under "Page with redirect" in GSC.
#
# These rules force 301 (permanent) so search engines collapse the slashed
# form into the canonical no-slash form and stop revisiting it.
#
# This list mirrors the public marketing, legal, auth, and resources routes.
# Authenticated app routes are intentionally omitted: they should be noindex'd
# and the 307 there has no SEO impact.
#
# When adding a new public route, add the trailing-slash entry here too.

/about/                /about                 301
/contact/              /contact               301
/pricing/              /pricing               301
/privacy/              /privacy               301
/resources/            /resources             301
/resources/amstar2/    /resources/amstar2     301
/resources/rob2/       /resources/rob2        301
/resources/robins-i/   /resources/robins-i    301
/security/             /security              301
/signin/               /signin                301
/signup/               /signup                301
/terms/                /terms                 301
